  "commentary": "**DEALER HEDGING COMMENTARY:**\n\nWith SPX at 6572 sitting right in the heart of massive negative gamma between 6550-6570 (all amplifying strikes), dealers are aggressively buying this rally as they're forced to hedge their short gamma positions. The breakout regime combined with -68B total GEX means any momentum will be amplified - dealers will continue buying strength toward the 6600 positive gamma wall where they'll flip to selling pressure. Watch 6560 as the max negative gamma strike where dealer buying pressure peaks, while 6600 represents the critical flip point where dealer hedging reverses from buying to selling.\n\n**Bottom line:** expect strong upward momentum until 6600 where selling pressure kicks in.",
